narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: There was some interesting stuff on time but mostly wasnt a great class. My writing did not improve at all over the semester and I think the whole class agreed he didnt offer much to help our writing.
I learned how many writing skills such as how to create citations and develop stronger arguments. Overall, I would say I become a better all around writer.
How to construct a proper academic essay
my abilities to write longer pieces and think critically about complex writing and philosophy

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course overall was a very pleasant course with loads of interesting readings and films. To improve the course, however, I lessen the number of philosophical readings required by the course.
Very repetitive however it made you think alot

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: No. If you are looking to improve as a writing, dont take this class. If you are looking for gut writing, take a different 114.

I would recommend the course to another student. Overall, it was very a very enjoyable and helpful course with the feedback you get from your peers and professor for your writings. Coming out, I can confidently say I am a better writer than I was coming in.
No, hard to comprehend and write solid essays about
